Package: splitdoor
Title: Calculate Causal Effects from Observational Time-series Data using the Split-door Criterion.
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Amit", "Sharma", email = "me@amitsharma.in", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Split-door criterion provides a method for identifying causal effect between two time-series. This R package provides functions for calculating causal effects from observational data using the split-door criterion.
For more details, see: Split-door criterion for causal identification: Automatic search for natural experiments. Amit Sharma, Jake Hofman, Duncan Watts.
https: //arxiv.org/abs/1611.09414
Depends: R (>= 3.3.2)
Imports: dplyr,
         ggplot2,
         cowplot,
         energy
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
